comments.text:
It's said that Lisanne had a leg sports injury before they set off for Panama. In the days they went on the Pianista trail, she was reportedly not feeling very well.
When her remains were tragically found, an autopsy showed a nasty infection that had got into her leg bone.
This would surely have been extremely painful, slowing her down. Perhaps Kris even tried to carry her ?  But i still suspect foul play re those boys, who died soon after the girls scattered remains were found.
If only they'd been carrying torches, whistles, flares that may have helped them escape and be rescued.
comments.author: @6543anjou
